Date: 6 Jul 2005
From: Natalia Pshenichnaya <crane@aaanet.ru>
Source: News agency Regnum [edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/480026.html>

Mushroom poisoning, Voronezh region, Russia
-----------------------------------------------
Since the end of June 2005, 19 people, including 3 children, have suffered
from mushroom poisoning in Voronezh and in other parts of the Voronezh
region, the Territorial Management of the Russian Consumer Supervision for
the Voronezh region stated.
Cases of mushroom poisoning have been registered in Voronezh (10 people)
and in 6 districts of the region (Anninskiy, Borysoglebskiy, Kashyrskiy,
Novokhoperskiy, Novousmanskiy, and Ternovskiy).
An inhabitant of Voronezh, who used the unknown mushrooms in food, has
died. As has been noted in the press services of the Territorial Management
of the Russian Consumer Supervision, the victims collected russulas, which
look like fairy-mushrooms.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
