Date: 6 Jul 2005
From: Natalia Pshenichnaya <crane@aaanet.ru>
Source: News agency Regnum [edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/480026.html>

Mushroom poisoning, Lipetsk region, Russia
-----------------------------------------------
16 people diagnosed with mushroom poisoning have been hospitalized in the
last week [1st week July 2005] in hospitals in the Lipetsk region. An
8-year-old girl has died from mushroom poisoning in the Izmalkovskiy
district of the region. The number of victims from the beginning of the
2005 mushroom season in the Lipetsk region has risen to 29 people, a
correspondent of Regnum with access to data from the Russian consumer
supervision reports.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The articles here indicate that poisoning by mushrooms is on the rise. But
the articles do not tell us much about clinical signs or the mushrooms
themselves.
In the United States, fairy mushrooms are generally regarded as toxic.
However, that is a common name not a scientific name. It is difficult to
know what species of mushrooms are being discussed when common names are
used. In one part of the country or the world, the term fairy mushroom may
not be associated with poisoning, while in other regions it may be. It is
always best, if possible, to know the scientific name to avoid confusion. -
Mod.TG]
